data.enText: a piece of soft cloth or paper that is folded around a baby's bottom and between its legs to absorb and hold its body waste
a disposable nappy (= one that is made to be used once only)

tr: garment consisting of a folded cloth drawn up between the legs and fastened at the waist
worn by infants to catch excrement

value.def: A nappy is a piece of soft thick cloth or paper which is fastened round a baby's bottom in order to soak up its urine and faeces.

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 diaper
